    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-10-13T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-10-13T03:00:00-05:00" n="635"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d635">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5592: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-13T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 13, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received Octover 13—5:24 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1185. Department’s written instruction 856, September 2, reporting <pb
                        facs="0677" n="579" xml:id="pg_579"/> conversation between <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_CWR1">Castle</persName> and Italian Ambassador on
                    August 25th.<note n="9" xml:id="d635fn9">Instruction No. 856 not printed; it
                        enclosed a copy of the memorandum of August 29, <ref target="#pg_573">p.
                            573</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>With reference to final paragraph of <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CWR1"
                        >Castle</persName>’s memorandum I have discussed matter with Military
                    Attaché and he has made discreet inquiries among all other Military Attachés who
                    participated in discussions regarding neutralization of Peiping and he reports
                    that no such proposal was made by the head of the Japanese Legation guard to any
                    of the various Military Attachés on that subject.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
